response.overview: NJPW Strong Style Symphony - New Japan Spirit 1999 event took place on April 10, 1999, at the Tokyo Dome in Tokyo, Japan. This professional wrestling spectacle features Keiji Muto defending the IWGP Heavyweight Championship against Don Frye in the main event. Other key matchups include Kensuke Sasaki & Shiro Koshinaka facing Genichiro Tenryu & Tatsumi Fujinami for the IWGP Tag Team titles, Koji Kanemoto challenging Shinjiro Otani for the IWGP Junior Heavyweight Championship, and a No Rope Explosive Barbed Wire Death Match between Masahiro Chono and Atsushi Onita. Additional bouts showcase Manabu Nakanishi & Yuji Nagata vs. nWo Japanâ€™s Hiroyoshi Tenzan & Satoshi Kojima and Jushin Liger & The Great Sasuke vs. Dr. Wagner Jr. & Kendo Kashin.
